claim.claim-text:
1. A device for measuring dimensions in a hollow organ of the body, comprising:
a length of conduit;
a measuring mechanism on one end of the conduit;
an indicator in connection with a second end of the conduit, the indicator being in operative connection with the measuring mechanism via a connector extending through the length of conduit and translating information of motion of the measuring mechanism to the indicator to provide an indication of a dimension measured by the measuring mechanism to a user of the device; and
a port for a viewing device on of the conduit to operatively connect a viewing device adapted to visualize of the area to be measured or the action of the measuring mechanism.
